ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would summarize it as a frustrating mandatory course.
I would not recommend it but it's required I think..
Yes. This course will give a new PhD student a good orientation before they start their thesis project. And this is a compulsory course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I did not learn much in this course.

Walther's lecture on image manipulation and Herve's lecture on jobs and funding opportunities were very helpful because they were so relevant. Some of the other topics had the potential to be relevant but the lectures were not helpful; some, like information on patents, was not at all applicable to me.
It tells me where to find resources when I need them

This course give me some knowledge that I hope to get for a long time such as how to apply for a grant,how to apply for a patent, how to analyze data anddo presentations. I feel more prepared to start my PhD thesis project after the course.
